7.  International Copy Editor and Desktop Publishing Specialist. Under the supervision of 
ADB’s Principal Water Supply and Sanitation Specialist in RSDD, the copy editor will be engaged 
for 2 person-months, to edit AWDO in accordance with ADB's editorial style. The copy editor will be 
responsible for typesetting and proofreading the text, tables, and changes from the preliminary 
draft to the final copy and filming the output before forwarding to the external printer. He or she will 
also be responsible for data linking to ensure data integrity and consistency in the final manuscript. 
The copy editor will convert the final report into PDF and html files for uploading to the ADB 
website. The copy editor must have full working knowledge of MS Office, Adobe Pagemaker and In 
Design, Photoshop, and a specialist art program, such as Coral Draw, Illustrator, or Freehand.  In 
particular, the copy-editor will: 

(i)  edit AWDO to ensure it conforms with ADB's editorial style and usage; 
(ii)  edit AWDO for consistency and accuracy; 
(iii)  edit the publication summary; 
(iv)  supervise the incorporation of corrections as well as of tables, charts, illustrations;  
(v)  edit the publication for balance; 
(vi)  review the final manuscript for filming; 
(vii)  prepare the glossary of terms and references; 
(viii)  edit all dissemination materials, including press releases, speeches, questions, and 
answers, key messages, and presentation slides;  
(ix)  convert desktop files to PDF and html formats, and perform other functions as may 
be assigned by RSDD staff. 

B.  APWF Media Coordinator  
8.  An international consultant (3 person-months) with expertise in public relations and public 
awareness, knowledge of water issues and of key actors will be engaged to assist the Japan Water 
Forum to promote the first APWS. The consultant will prepare and implement an international 
public outreach strategy comprising promotional materials and public awareness and advocacy 
tools for the first APWS and to promote the AWDO. The consultant will work closely with the Japan 
Water Forum (JWF) and ADB staff from the Department of External Relations and RSDD. The 
consultant will coordinate all media activities related to APWF in the lead up to and during the 
APWS, including the following: 

(i)  in coordination with ADB and JWF, draw up a media plan for the APWS and the 
preparations for it; 
(ii)  identify and carry out options for pre-event publicity in international and local press 
in the region in order to increase the visibility of the APWF and AWDO and ensure 
its messages make an impact; 
(iii)  develop media contacts for the event; 
(iv)  draw up a media list and send out media invitations for the APWS and AWDO; 
(v)  coordinate the activities of a small media team recruited for the APWF;  
(vi)  organize all press events (e.g., interviews, news conferences, and launches) for the 
APWF; 
(vii)  coordinate  and/or  write  official  press  releases  before  and  during  the  APWS  in 
English and Japanese; and 
(viii)  coordinate website materials for the APWF, including speeches, presentations, and 
news releases, including translations where appropriate.
